issue.title: Lots of minor doc improvements

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
* DirectML Execution Provider
   * Fix page title
   * Link to official DirectML documentation
   * Remove unnecessary white space
* Install
  * Remove fixed version from donet commands
  * Remove unnecessary white space
* Graph optimization
  * Capitalize CPU and CUDA
  * Document how to enable GELU Approximation
  * Hide details about BERT approximation optimizations
  * Document how to use an already-optimized model to reduce startup
    time.
  * Minor fixes for clarity and organization
* High level design
  * Minor fixes for clarity and organization
  * Condense section on "Using the NuGet WinRT API with other C-API distributions"

body: Thanks for pointing this out @garymm! Do you have a customer usage scenario for these changes? i,e. did you figure this out because you were trying to answer a specific question? Any more detail would be appreciated as we try and improve this
No. I was reading the High Level Design page for my own education and I found the existing organization confusing.
